social_posts.post_text: Friends + laughter making the holidays so special and such a time to remember!  Love you all…Part 1 (there are so many good photos!)
Part 2!  The party continues….
Merry Xmas and Happy Holidays, friends!  Loving all of this fam time!
Enjoyed the last moments of 2022….Happy New Year to you and all and looking forward to an amazing 2023!!
Just a bit of Spring Break 2023.  Took me so long to post!

Last night!  I am so proud to be a Board member of @dancetheatreofharlem, and last night could not have been more special - from the unbelievable Dougla performance, to honoring the inimitable @virginia_johnsondth (and me tearing up congratulating her!! 🥹) to our largest level of support for the gala to date!  This has been the most beautiful evolution, and I count myself fortunate to be part of it!
My littlest monkey is turning 4 today, and I am overcome!  We are never not celebrating you, Aslani (and did alllll weekend!). Your spirit and energy changes everything around you!! ❤️❤️❤️
This is F I F T E E N!  Happy Anniversary, my ❤️‍🔥. That first clip was Vegas 2003 when we were babieeeees, and they go all the way through last month.  I may be the 🌞, but you are my 🌍.
Happy Mother’s Day to all who mother sending lots of ❤️❤️❤️❤️ today and all days!
My sweetheart turns 10 today!  She continues to fill our life with such light and joy - how lucky are we!
Lately…

All ready to start the party to celebrate @parrishartmuseum’s 125th anniversary!  Tonight we are going to dance the night away and tomorrow night’s Midsummer Magic gala is going to be one for the books!!

And that’s a wrap on what was an epic night celebrating 125 years of the @parrishartmuseum!  I was fortunate enough to get to co-chair the Midsummer Gala with @debbiebancroftny and honor @sammemoyer, Eddie Martinez, and @hankwillisthomas.  Could not have been happier by all of the support.  Thank you to @maxmara @bankofamerica @wolfferwine @boisson.sips @patron @gt_law for sponsoring, @fremontblueevents  for a the most amazing event planning, @canardinc and @maerzryan for delicious food, @natiemusic  for killing it on the violin, @djmos for keeping us dancing late into the night, @frankalexandernyc for gorgeous design, @kamaalicouture for the 🔥 outfit, @nychennaqueen for the mehndi artistry, and of course my people @kmp.nyc @joy__p_ @iammikemuse @jessicaasteiner @sealesbelelieu for being there above all!

LOVE @ourselfskin and had so much fun that day!!

If you have followed me for some time, you may know I have been working on a project so near and dear to my heart, Issa’s Edible Adventures.  What started as a seed of a story evolved into an app I launched on the App Store and which Apple miraculously featured!  From there, it was testing it out in schools, the @bklynlibrary, @nysci and even @columbia. 

I went through so much development from character designs to stories to even production partners, and I am so so proud to announce this partnership with @toonzmediagroup and Epic Story Media.  Having these two powerful teams, we have created something bigger and better than I could have imagined and will begin with an animated series and build to books, toys, games and more.  Check out the link in my bio for more and please follow @issasedibleadventures !  Also, stay tuned and I promise to keep sharing the evolution!

Had tea today with the lovely @royashariat and @gitajoons, the duo behind @mamanandme on the eve of their cookbook release!  It’s such a beautiful ode to family and culture and left me inspired for the day.  It was their day and they gave me their own blended tea and the most fragrant saffron!!! Congratulations to you both and everyone else grab a copy of Maman & Me!

Last night was quintessential New York - where art, food and culture came together in the most beautiful way. Dance Theatre of Harlem performed @worksandprocess @guggenheim.  THE @robertgarland gave us an inside view into the thought process, nuances and contextualization behind the gorgeous and moving (I cried 🙋🏽‍♀️) dances along with four, illustrious DTH alumnae - Dionne Figgins (Director, Ballet Tech); Alicia Graf Mack (Director, Juilliard School Dance Division); Tai Jimenez (Director, Dance Theatre of Harlem School); and Melanie Person (Co-Director, The Ailey School, and Director, Ailey/Fordham BFA). 

We also had an amazing dinner @themarkrestaurantnyc @themarkhotelny where I got to play my small part - choosing a super delicious menu with equally yummy wine pairings.  The vibe, the conversation, the whole experience was so special and memorable, but, most importantly, due to the people that were there.  Thank you @annaglass @sharonyduncan @alphamom @leslie_alicewims @tmuldrow @kinjil @vimlamanycolors @jrobertwood1 @natashallikesthis @rcbowen @sealesbelelieu and many others for making the night so dynamic. ❤️❤️❤️

ALSO, one of the dances was set to this song, thus.

Although I didn’t celebrate Diwali growing up, it always struck me as something to which we all could relate and celebrate in our own ways- the triumph of light over darkness and knowledge over ignorance. 

From the most stunning #NewYorkDiwaliGala @mo_newyork hosted by the equally stunning @alvinapatel and @maneeshkgoyal to kids’ Diwali parties with fam and friends, it has been quite the season.

Thank you to @kamaalicouture, @thegempalace, and @sidkas for the serious DRIP. 🥰

Had THE almost fun today on the 3rd hour of @todayshow making Trini Macaroni Pie (a baked macaroni and cheese with onions, garlic and scotch bonnets!) and Ponche de Crème (a Trini “eggnog” with spices, lime zest and bitters). A true love of mine is cooking for the holidays and incorporating the mosaic of cultures that are part of my unique family in all of that good cooking!  I think @sheinelle_o, @alroker and @dylandreyernbc enjoyed the dishes…check the link in my bio for their real-time reactions! A special thank you to @katie.stilo for making me look good and to @jessicaasteiner for being my ride-or-die😊.

Just wanted to share a few photos from an absolutely stunning dinner last week with @theeverycompany @elevenmadisonpark and @danielhumm.  We were amongst the first to taste the world’s first vegan egg, prepared by the amazing chefs at Eleven Madison Park and it did not disappoint!
